LAGOS – Former Governor of Ogun State, Senator Ibikunle Amosun, who currently represents Ogun Central Senatorial District has written the Senate, declaring his intention to contest the 2023 Presidential election on the platform of the ruling All Progressives Congress (APC). The letter was read on Wednesday during plenary by the President of the Senate, Senator Ahmad Lawan. Amosun is expected to formally make the announcement on May 5 in Abuja Details later…